election_record.label: New Hampshire 1824 U.S. House of Representatives

overview.note: New Hampshire law required a majority to elect for the U.S. House of Representatives. A 2nd Trial would be held on March 8, 1825.

"Eleven towns were rejected from informality in the returns. From four towns, returns were not received. The choice will be made for one vacancy from EZEKIEL WEBSTER, and JOSEPH HEALY, the two candidates having the highest number of votes, not chosen: by law, a plurality only will be necessary at the next trial." Concord Register (Concord, NH). December 4, 1824.
